Day 3 - I embrace my little T-Rex like arms, I embrace my full rounded belly, I embrace that Yoga is MY journey - there is no right, there is no wrong - I am here, I am present, I only ask of myself that I try. Something that seems so simple, cross arms and touch my knees - made me break out in a giggle cuz it was such a challenge - my mind, body and soul all found such light and humor in this movement. You know often its been my mind tell my body - your this, your that (negative thoughts) - it's rare when all 3 align and agree to relax, enjoy the moment and laugh out loud! Thank you for letting me embrace ALL that is ME! Namaste!

Hi Adriene, I wanted to write my sincere thanks for your videos! I've been following you for a few months now and I really enjoy your practice. Glad I found this Yoga Camp and excited to continue (albeit a few days behind everyone else :0))

Last year I tried your 30 days of yoga videos and quit because they were too easy (not to say there wouldn't have in reality been good emotional and physical reasons to stick with it). However, in September I had a closed head injury leading to three weeks unconscious plus Acute Respiratory Distress Syndrome after an infection caused by swallowing some vomit into my lungs after the accident so about two months in bed all and all and another few weeks in inpatient rehabilitation. I lost all the strength and flexibility I took for granted before the accident and had to learn to walk again. This has been really really perfect for where I'm at right now... What before my accident the jerk in me would have said was too easy to bother with is now sometimes a little on the hard side, but you do a good of giving alternatives that I am able to do. Since you not the kind of instructor who is constantly saying one should just stick with it even if it's hard I don't feel as bad and frustrated when I have to take a break as I might otherwise. I am really grateful for having this to do as part of my recovery. I hope if I do get the strength and flexibility back I used to have (which may or may not happen) I'm smart enough to stick with some yoga that isn't just about the physical, this is helping rebuild my emotional strength as well.
